<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>



<title>SIMPLE-REMOVE-LINK-DECISION</title>

</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I decide whether to break a link with another player.</i> </h3>

	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	</p>
	<p><b>SIMPLE-REMOVE-LINK-DECISION</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>if link-neighbor? my-other-player
   [set my-remove-link-utility-gain
        utility-of-network [] (list my-other-player) -
        utility-of-network [] []
    set my-decision-to-unlink my-remove-link-utility-gain &gt; 0]
</pre>
	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>
	<p>
	<a title="SIMPLE-ADD-LINK-DECISION" href="SIMPLE-ADD-LINK-DECISION.html">
	SIMPLE-ADD-LINK-DECISION</a> decides whether to add a link if none exists.
	This uses

	<a title="UTILITY-OF-NETWORK" href="UTILITY-OF-NETWORK.html">

	UTILITY-OF-NETWORK</a> to compute the utility of the current network and the 
	network with some additions and removals.</p>
	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>If the player I'm paired with is one of my links then if the utility of 
	the network without the other player is greater I arrange for the link to be 
	broken when <a href="REMOVE-A-LINK-IF-DECIDED.html">REMOVE-A-LINK-IF-DECIDED</a>
	runs. This also records <i>my-remove-link-utility-gain</i> which can be used 
	to gather statistics.</p>
	<h2>History</h2>

	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn.
</body>
</html>

